CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. B7 reads: "6. The happiest person a...was grand prize winner Lavine Robinson of 407 Robinson Court....1960 gas dryer, was proudly presented by Harold Mason, representative...Noraella Brown, home service representative for the Peoples Natural Gas Company."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of grand prize winner Lavine Robinson, on right, with Harold Mason and Noraella Brown standing in Syria Mosque for the 1960 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama
